:: Start [index] {"position":"0,0","size":"180,120"}
# ZORK I LEGOS STATEGRAPH

This Twee file turns the Zork LEGOS decomposition into a loadable Twine graph.

The rule: do not make twenty-one CINEOSIS images for every atom. Load the atoms, then select a state unit. ABC CINEOSIS expands one selected state unit into PAST / PRESENT / FUTURE image matrices when needed.

<div class="legos-card">
Core path:

* [[State Units]]
* [[Atom Index]]
* [[Timeline Phases]]
* [[Operator Load]]
* [[Engine Contract]]
* [[Validator Checklist]]
* [[LEGOS Engine JSON]]
</div>

Start the playable/filmable chain here: [[SU 01 Surface House]]

:: Engine Contract [index] {"position":"220,0","size":"180,120"}
# Engine Contract

The engine consumes a selected `state_unit`, not the whole document.

Each state unit carries:

* LEGOS atom references.
* A PAST state.
* A PRESENT action.
* A FUTURE consequence.
* An ABC CINEOSIS seed.

The engine then expands that selected unit into:

* premise
* temporal engine
* ABC model
* 21-image matrix
* shot sequence
* sound map
* edit map
* BEFLIX if requested

[[Start]]

:: Operator Load [index] {"position":"440,0","size":"220,150"}
# Operator Load

Use the companion file:

`legos-zork-scenes.json`

In OP-08 Operator:

Save → Load file → choose `legos-zork-scenes.json`

Operator will load each Zork state unit as a separate BEFLIX branch from the root.

Twee can also carry BEFLIX directly using this pattern, which Operator now understands:

```html
<!-- BEFLIX
C SCENE Name
CLR 0
PNT 20 20 20 20 7
REC 4
/BEFLIX -->
```

Twine ignores the comment. Operator extracts it.

[[Start]]

:: State Units [index] {"position":"0,170","size":"220,180"}
# State Units

These are the LEGO clusters the engine should compose from.

1. [[SU 01 Surface House]]
2. [[SU 02 Light Darkness]]
3. [[SU 03 Troll Gate]]
4. [[SU 04 Maze Grating]]
5. [[SU 05 Cyclops Gate]]
6. [[SU 06 Thief Economy]]
7. [[SU 07 Egg Canary Bauble]]
8. [[SU 08 Temple Hades]]
9. [[SU 09 Dam Reservoir]]
10. [[SU 10 River Rainbow]]
11. [[SU 11 Mine Gas Basket]]
12. [[SU 12 Machine Diamond]]
13. [[SU 13 Loud Room]]
14. [[SU 14 Trophy Endgame]]

[[Start]]

:: SU 01 Surface House [state-unit] {"position":"260,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 01 — Surface House

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_whouse_w`, `loc_kitchen`, `loc_living`, `loc_attic`, `loc_cellar`  
entities: `ent_adv`, `ent_lamp_leaf`, `ent_lamp`, `ent_sword`, `ent_rug`, `ent_trapdr`  
obstacles: concealed entry, unarmed descent, unknown underground  
shifts: `sh_descend`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the house is already a sealed interface to an older empire; the mailbox and leaflet are residue from prior adventurers.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the adventurer reads, enters, takes lamp and sword, lifts the rug, and opens the trapdoor.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: descent commits the player to darkness, one-way movement, and treasure recovery.</div>

ABC seed: a nameless body crosses from domestic surface into subterranean machine-space; rug, lamp, sword, window, and trapdoor become a temporal hinge.

<div class="nav">[[State Units]] · [[next->SU 02 Light Darkness]]</div>

:: SU 02 Light Darkness [state-unit] {"position":"540,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 02 — Light / Darkness

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: all dark rooms  
entities: `ent_lamp`, `ent_torch`, `ent_grue`, `ent_adv`  
goals: `g_light`, `g_survive`  
obstacles: `o_dark`, `o_battery`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the underground already contains darkness as a predator; earlier bodies failed where light failed.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the lamp burns down while the adventurer chooses routes, carrying finite safety through rooms that erase the map.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: permanent torchlight or death by grue; every delay becomes visible as battery loss.</div>

ABC seed: light is not decoration; it is a consumable body. The film watches the lamp become time.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 01 Surface House]] · [[next->SU 03 Troll Gate]]</div>

:: SU 03 Troll Gate [state-unit] {"position":"820,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 03 — Troll Gate

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_troll`, `loc_cellar`, `loc_roundroom`  
entities: `ent_adv`, `ent_troll`, `ent_sword`  
obstacles: `o_troll`  
shifts: `sh_troll`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the passage has been held by force before the player arrives; the troll is a living lock.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: sword and body confront axe and appetite; movement through the map requires violence.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the gate opens, but the empire teaches that tools solve space by changing bodies.</div>

ABC seed: a narrow room compresses map logic into combat; the sword glints before a tunnel becomes passable.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 02 Light Darkness]] · [[next->SU 04 Maze Grating]]</div>

:: SU 04 Maze Grating [state-unit] {"position":"1100,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 04 — Maze / Grating

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_maze`, `loc_grating`, `loc_clearing`  
entities: `ent_adv`, `ent_skeleton`, `ent_keys`  
obstacles: `o_maze`  
relations: mapping through dropped objects; key opens grate
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the skeleton proves the maze has already consumed another route-maker.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the adventurer turns spatial confusion into a readable graph by marking, testing, and recovering the key.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the grating creates a surface shortcut and changes the underground from trap into network.</div>

ABC seed: repetition becomes legible only when objects are sacrificed as markers.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 03 Troll Gate]] · [[next->SU 05 Cyclops Gate]]</div>

:: SU 05 Cyclops Gate [state-unit] {"position":"1380,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 05 — Cyclops Gate

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_cyclops`, `loc_treasure`, `loc_living`  
entities: `ent_adv`, `ent_cyclops`  
obstacles: `o_cyclops`  
shifts: `sh_ulysses`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: myth is stored as a password; the cyclops carries an old story as a vulnerability.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the player speaks the right name and language acts physically on the map.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the cyclops flees and breaks open a shortcut; speech becomes architecture.</div>

ABC seed: a monster's memory is stronger than its body; a word opens a wall.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 04 Maze Grating]] · [[next->SU 06 Thief Economy]]</div>

:: SU 06 Thief Economy [state-unit] {"position":"1660,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 06 — Thief Economy

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_maze`, `loc_treasure`  
entities: `ent_adv`, `ent_thief`, `ent_case`  
goals: `g_case`, `g_thief`  
obstacles: `o_thief`  
shifts: `sh_killthief`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the thief has already built a parallel economy of stolen treasure.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the player and thief compete for the same objects; inventory becomes unstable.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: defeating the thief returns dispersed treasure and stabilizes the trophy case path.</div>

ABC seed: the antagonist is not merely blocking; he edits the location of value.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 05 Cyclops Gate]] · [[next->SU 07 Egg Canary Bauble]]</div>

:: SU 07 Egg Canary Bauble [state-unit] {"position":"1940,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 07 — Egg / Canary / Bauble

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_uptree`, `loc_forest`, `loc_treasure`  
entities: `t_egg`, `t_canary`, `t_bauble`, `ent_thief`  
obstacles: `o_fragile`  
shifts: `sh_canary`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the jeweled egg encloses another mechanism; value is nested inside value.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the player cannot safely open the egg, so the thief must act on it first.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the canary is wound, a bird answers, and the bauble falls into the world.</div>

ABC seed: the correct action is delayed authorship; let the enemy transform the fragile object.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 06 Thief Economy]] · [[next->SU 08 Temple Hades]]</div>

:: SU 08 Temple Hades [state-unit] {"position":"2220,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 08 — Temple / Hades

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_temple`, `loc_altar`, `loc_entrhades`, `loc_hades`  
entities: `ent_bell`, `ent_book`, `ent_candles`, `ent_spirits`, `t_skull`  
obstacles: `o_spirits`  
shifts: `sh_exorcism`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: ritual objects preserve a prior covenant with the dead.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: bell, book, and candle are sequenced into a visible rite that changes an invisible barrier.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the spirits clear, the skull is claimable, and death becomes an inventory problem.</div>

ABC seed: sound, flame, text, and bone convert a blocked threshold into a room.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 07 Egg Canary Bauble]] · [[next->SU 09 Dam Reservoir]]</div>

:: SU 09 Dam Reservoir [state-unit] {"position":"2500,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 09 — Dam / Reservoir

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_damroom`, `loc_damlobby`, `loc_maint`, `loc_resv_s`, `loc_resv`, `loc_resv_n`  
entities: `ent_adv`, `ent_wrench`, `t_trunk`  
obstacles: `o_water`  
shifts: `sh_drain`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the reservoir holds a drowned route and a hidden treasure under managed water.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: button, bolt, wrench, and control panel make infrastructure visible as puzzle grammar.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the waterline drops; the trunk appears; traversal and treasure state both change.</div>

ABC seed: an old dam edits geography. Water is the obstacle, archive, and reveal.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 08 Temple Hades]] · [[next->SU 10 River Rainbow]]</div>

:: SU 10 River Rainbow [state-unit] {"position":"2780,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 10 — River / Rainbow

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_riverside`, `loc_river1`, `loc_sandy`, `loc_aragain`, `loc_endrainbow`  
entities: `ent_boat`, `ent_pump`, `ent_shovel`, `ent_sceptre`, `t_emerald`, `t_scarab`, `t_pot`  
shifts: `sh_rainbow`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: river motion already imposes one-way time; the rainbow is visible but not yet solid.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: inflate boat, travel downstream, dig sand, recover hidden objects, wave sceptre.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: color becomes bridge; the pot of gold appears where optics become architecture.</div>

ABC seed: a fragile vehicle carries the player through irreversible water toward a bridge made from light.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 09 Dam Reservoir]] · [[next->SU 11 Mine Gas Basket]]</div>

:: SU 11 Mine Gas Basket [state-unit] {"position":"3060,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 11 — Mine / Gas / Basket

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_squeaky`, `loc_shaft`, `loc_gasroom`, `loc_drafty`, `loc_coalmine`  
entities: `ent_garlic`, `ent_bat`, `ent_lamp`, `ent_torch`, `ent_coal`, `t_bracelet`  
obstacles: `o_bat`, `o_gas`, `o_carry`  
shifts: `sh_garlic`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the mine is built around constraints: narrow passages, gas, baskets, and prior industrial danger.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: garlic changes the bat, lamp replaces flame, and the basket moves objects where the body cannot.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: the player can reach the machine path with coal and safe light, but only by obeying material limits.</div>

ABC seed: the body is too large, flame is forbidden, and the basket becomes a second body.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 10 River Rainbow]] · [[next->SU 12 Machine Diamond]]</div>

:: SU 12 Machine Diamond [state-unit] {"position":"3340,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 12 — Machine / Diamond

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_machine`, `loc_drafty`  
entities: `ent_coal`, `ent_screw`, `t_diamond`  
goals: `g_diamond`  
shifts: `sh_diamond`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the machine preserves empire technology as an idle transformation engine.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: coal is inserted; the screwdriver activates the switch; pressure converts material state.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: coal becomes diamond; industrial action becomes treasure.</div>

ABC seed: black mineral enters a machine and returns as compressed light.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 11 Mine Gas Basket]] · [[next->SU 13 Loud Room]]</div>

:: SU 13 Loud Room [state-unit] {"position":"3620,170","size":"240,180"}
# SU 13 — Loud Room

<div class="legos-card">
LEGOS atoms:

locations: `loc_loud`  
entities: `t_bar`  
obstacles: `o_loud`  
shifts: `sh_echo`
</div>

<div class="past">PAST: the room has turned language into uncontrolled repetition.</div>

<div class="present">PRESENT: the command `echo` names the room's behavior and cancels it.</div>

<div class="future">FUTURE: sound quiets; the platinum bar becomes obtainable.</div>

ABC seed: a room that repeats commands is silenced when it hears its own mechanism named.

<div class="nav">[[prev->SU 12 Machine Diamond]] · [[next->SU 14 Trophy Endgame]]</div>

