[[Atom Index]]

:: Goals [atom] {"position":"900,420","size":"260,180"}
# Goals

* `g_master`: become Master Adventurer.
* `g_case`: fill the trophy case with all treasures.
* `g_light`: maintain light source.
* `g_survive`: survive thief, troll, cyclops, bat, grue.
* `g_drain`: drain the reservoir.
* `g_exorcise`: clear Hades.
* `g_rainbow`: make the rainbow solid.
* `g_diamond`: transmute coal into diamond.
* `g_thief`: antagonist goal; hoard treasures.

[[Atom Index]]

:: Obstacles [atom] {"position":"1200,420","size":"280,220"}
# Obstacles

* `o_dark`: darkness / grue death.
* `o_battery`: finite lamp battery.
* `o_thief`: thief steals and relocates treasure.
* `o_troll`: troll blocks passage.
* `o_cyclops`: cyclops blocks stair.
* `o_maze`: maze disorients.
* `o_water`: reservoir blocks access.
* `o_spirits`: spirits guard Hades.
* `o_gas`: open flame explodes in gas room.
* `o_bat`: bat abducts.
* `o_carry`: inventory and body-size constraints.
* `o_loud`: commands echo.
* `o_fragile`: egg / painting fragility.

[[Atom Index]]

:: Shifts [atom] {"position":"1520,420","size":"300,260"}
# Shifts

* `sh_descend`: enter underground; trapdoor slams.
* `sh_troll`: slay troll; passage opens.
* `sh_ulysses`: speak myth-name; cyclops flees and breaks shortcut.
* `sh_drain`: operate dam; reservoir drains.
* `sh_exorcism`: bell / book / candle ritual; Hades opens.
* `sh_canary`: thief opens egg; canary summons bauble.
* `sh_killthief`: defeat thief; recover stolen treasure.
* `sh_rainbow`: wave sceptre; rainbow becomes bridge.
* `sh_diamond`: coal through machine; diamond appears.
* `sh_echo`: say echo; loud room quiets.
* `sh_garlic`: carry garlic; bat does not abduct.
* `sh_win`: deposit final treasure; Stone Barrow map appears.

[[Atom Index]]

:: Relations [atom] {"position":"1860,420","size":"340,300"}
# Relations

Key morphisms:

* `[descends_into] ent_adv -> loc_cellar`
* `[seeks] ent_adv -> ent_case`
* `[bars_passage] ent_troll -> ent_adv`
* `[blocks] ent_cyclops -> ent_adv`
* `[steals_from] ent_thief -> ent_adv`
* `[competes_with] ent_thief -> ent_adv`
* `[devours] ent_grue -> ent_adv`
* `[abducts] ent_bat -> ent_adv`
* `[repelled_by] ent_bat -> ent_garlic`
* `[guards] ent_spirits -> t_skull`
* `[contains] ent_case -> all treasures`
* `[contains] t_egg -> t_canary`
* `[contains] t_coffin -> t_sceptre2`
* `[opens_safely] ent_thief -> t_egg`
* `[transmutes] loc_machine -> t_diamond`
* `[solidifies] ent_sceptre -> loc_aragain`
* `[fears] ent_cyclops -> Ulysses/Odysseus`
* `[illuminates] ent_lamp -> any location`
* `[illuminates] ent_torch -> any location permanently`
* `[ignites] ent_match -> ent_candles`
* `[drains] loc_damroom -> loc_resv`
* `[returns_to] loc_studio -> loc_kitchen`

[[Atom Index]]

:: State Axes [atom] {"position":"2240,420","size":"320,240"}
# State Axes

Use axes instead of enumerating every possible permutation.

<pre class="legos-data">room_access:
  [unknown, seen, lit, dark, blocked, opened, transformed, one_way, exhausted]
object_location:
  [world, carried, container, hidden, revealed, stolen, destroyed, deposited]
treasure_lifecycle:
  [unfound, revealed, obtainable, carried, stolen, recovered, deposited, transformed]
antagonist:
  [latent, encountered, active, displaced, defeated, useful]
obstacle:
  [latent, blocking, prepared, solved, failed]
light:
  [none, lantern_on, lantern_low, torch_on, darkness_death]
inventory_constraint:
  [free, overloaded, must_drop, sharp_object_puncture, open_flame_forbidden]
timeline_phase:
  [surface, descent, hub_open, temple, dam, river, mine, thief_resolution, endgame]</pre>

[[Atom Index]]

:: Timeline Phases [index] {"position":"0,700","size":"320,260"}
# Timeline Phases

* `ph0`: Surface Prologue — leaflet, house, lamp, sword, rug, trapdoor.
* `ph1`: First Descent — cellar, shut trapdoor, troll.
* `ph2`: Temple / Hades — bell, book, candles, skull.
* `ph3`: Dam / River — control panel, reservoir, boat, scarab, emerald, rainbow, pot.
* `ph4`: Coal Mine / Diamond — garlic, bat, gas, basket, machine.
* `ph5`: Thief / Egg — thief opens egg, thief defeated, canary yields bauble.
* `ph6`: Endgame — all treasures deposited, Stone Barrow appears.

[[Start]]

:: Validator Checklist [validator] {"position":"360,700","size":"340,280"}
# Validator Checklist

Before this drives an engine:

1. Every id is unique.
2. Every referenced id exists.
3. Every treasure has a lifecycle path ending in `deposited`.
4. Every obstacle has at least one resolving shift.
5. Every shift has preconditions and postconditions.
6. Every state unit has `past`, `present`, and `future`.
7. Every state unit names concrete visible material for ABC CINEOSIS.
8. Map edges are explicit; generic maze / river summaries are not enough for runtime navigation.
9. Duplicate aliases are resolved.
10. Missing atoms are added: `loc_loud`, `loc_stone_barrow`, exact maze cells, exact river cells.

[[Start]]

